/*!
\page rdlss How to simulate basic galaxy properties <B>with clustering</B>: <CODE>rdlss</CODE>


 EXAMPLE 1: Simulate a galaxy catalog from an over-density distribution<BR>
            in file odens.fits.  We want the survey to have a circular sky area with<BR>
            radius = pi/4 radians, and galaxies with randomized positions in the pixels.<BR>
            So not to produce too many galaxies so the absolute magnitude cut is set,<BR>
            This throws out any galaxies with an unobservable absolute magnitude given<BR>
            their redshifts. This is simulation number 1 so the id is set to be 1.<BR>
            The output catalog will be saved to out.fits:<BR>
	
            <CODE>$ rdlss -C odens.fits -O out.fits -a 0.7854 -i 1 -R -M</CODE><BR>
	
 EXAMPLE 2: Similar to example 1, but write only the true redshifts<BR>
            to the galaxy catalog and DON'T set the absolute magnitude cut:<BR>

            <CODE>$ rdlss -C odens.fits -O ztrue.fits -i 1 -R -Z</CODE><BR>
            
            
Below are the usage instructions

<CODE>Usage: rdlss [...options...]
      
 -O : OutputFileName: filename that the output is written to <BR>
 -a : SkyArea: Radius of survey sky area in radians (assumed circular) [default=2PI]<BR>
 -C : MassDistFileName: FITS filename containing SimLSS output<BR>
 -H : Only produce a histogram of the TRUE catalog n(z) [default=NO]<BR>
 -i : Simulation identifier, integer >=1 [default=1]<BR>
 -M : Don't add galaxies with M>AbsMagCut(z) [default=YES]<BR>
 -N : OutRoot: Output mass cube, ngals cube to files [OutRoot]_ngals.fits<BR>
      and [OutRoot]_mass.fits [default=NO,OutRoot=tmp]<BR>
 -R : Randomise galaxy positions within cell [default=NO]<BR>
 -S : Only do a simple sim of ra,dec,z [default=NO]<BR>
 -s : ngal: Another type of simple simulation. Simulate ngal galaxies in each cell [default=NO,ngal=1]<BR>
 -x : xplanes: Number of SimLSS cube planes to remove [default=1]<BR>
 -z : z dimension is 'radial' direction [default=NO]<BR>
 -Z : Only produce a catalog containing the TRUE redshifts (and galaxy IDs)<BR>;
     [default=NO] </CODE><BR>

*/
